betterquesting.name: Getting Wood
betterquesting.desc:
Wooden vanilla tools are not very effective in this world. 

Perhaps punching some grass to aquire enough materials to craft some crude tools would be a good idea!

Once you have chopped down a tree, turn 1 log into a chopping board. Place the board, add some logs and hit them with your axe to aquire planks. You can do the same with planks to aquire sticks. The better the tool, the more you planks and sticks you will get.

betterquesting.name: Basic Tools
betterquesting.desc: With a bit more fibre and flint, you are able to craft other crude tools as well.

betterquesting.name: Drinking Water
betterquesting.desc: I'm sure drinking dirty river water is a ton of fun, but perhaps it's time to look into some cleaner water. The cleaner it is, the more thirst it will quench.

betterquesting.name: Improved Water
betterquesting.desc:
Bottles don't hold much liquid, so why not upgrade to a canteen?
And while you are at it, rain collectors are a great way of saving up clean rain water.

betterquesting.name: Juicy
betterquesting.desc: Drinking water everyday can be quite boring, so why not try some other drinks? Only the best for the best!

betterquesting.name: Automated Saw
betterquesting.desc:
Dispensers can place blocks infront of the saw.

Build a redstone clock by placing a block above a turntable and attach a redstone torch to the side of that block.

betterquesting.name: Keeping Track
betterquesting.desc: Keeping track of the current season and temperature is a great way to not turn into a flaming ball of fire.

betterquesting.name: Extra Life
betterquesting.desc:
Life crystals increase your overall health by one heart (not to be confused with the BetterQuesting lifes).

The world is full of old ruins and chests that can contain crystals.

betterquesting.name: Camping
betterquesting.desc:
It can get quite cold at night. Nothing a lit campfire couldn't solve though!

Once you placed the campfire, right click with sticks to ignite it. This may require several tries.

betterquesting.name: Better Crafting Bench
betterquesting.desc: Unlike the vanilla crafting bench, this one keeps the items on the crafting grid when closing the UI.

betterquesting.name: Stockpiles
betterquesting.desc:
An easy (and awesome looking) way of storing all your riches is by using Impractical Storage.
Items that get pumped into the controller will be placed/displayed in the pre-defined storage area (which you can adjust by right clicking the controller). At the same time you can also pull items out of the system again.

Perhaps you can come up with a nice inventory system for this?
